END-->    )<br><br>All you have to do is attend a language fair being held on Sunday, April 7th.  At a minimum, some milk and cookies will be provided.  As more goodies become available, this message will be updated.  Gnomes, or any other race, do not count as goodies to the Iksar, Ogres, and Trolls out there – at least during the language fair.<br><br>So far, the only requirements are that you set aside your differences for a few hours, learn the language you desire, and try to have a bit of fun.<br><br>Several guilds will be joining together for this event, and I will update information as more confirm their participation.  So far we have:<br><br>Chosen of Vah<br>Circle of Sisters<br>Twilight Bastion<br><br><br>Event Details:<br><br>Date: Sunday April 7th<br>Time:  4-6pm EST; 3-5pm CST; 2-4pm MST; 1-3 pm PST<br>Location:  East Commonlands/North Ro Tunnel<br><br>Several languages will be taught, come visit us to see if a specific language you want is being taught, or to ask that someone teach it.  Check back here for updates, or visit ( <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub59.ezboard.com/ftwilightbastionfrm1.showMessage?topicID=21.topic">pub59.ezboard.com/ftwilig...D=21.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ) for more questions and answers. <br><br>Hope to see you there, and perhaps be able to converse with you afterwards!<br><br><br>Goest Woodwalker<br>Ambassador of Twilight Bastion<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugoestwoodwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goest Woodwalker</A> at: 4/3/02 10:33:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=silvanoshae>Silvanoshae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/1/02 9:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScre